                            <comment id="12930871" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 11 Nov 2010 00:51:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch survived an onslaught of disabling/enabling mixed with massive imports. It unassigns the daughter regions when the RS checks in with the split message if the table is disabled/disabling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12930873" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 11 Nov 2010 00:55:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the record, this kind of stuff was impossible in the old master. Really exciting that it&apos;s finally fixed!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12930936" author="stack" created="Thu, 11 Nov 2010 05:59:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Small patch.  Go commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12930940" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 11 Nov 2010 06:17:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Stack, I committed this to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017161" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:42:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
